<inglise> Council Regulation (EC) No 1091/2001 of 28 May 2001 on freedom of movement with a long-stay visa </inglise>
<eesti> N&Otilde;UKOGU M&Auml;&Auml;RUS (E&Uuml;) nr 1091/2001 liikumisvabaduse kohta pikaajalise viisa alusel 28. mai 2001 </eesti>
<inglise> THE COUNCIL OF THE EUROPEAN UNION, </inglise>
<eesti> EUROOPA LIIDU N&Otilde;UKOGU, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Community, and in particular Articles 62(2) (b) (ii) and 63(3) (a) thereof, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa &Uuml;henduse asutamislepingut, eriti selle artikli 62 l&otilde;ike 2 punkti b alapunkti ii ja artikli 63 l&otilde;ike 3 punkti a, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the initiative of the French Republic(1), </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Prantsuse Vabariigi algatust, (1) </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the opinion of the European Parliament(2), </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa Parlamendi arvamust (2) </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas: </inglise>
<eesti> ning arvestades, et: </eesti>
<inglise> (1) There may be a time lag between the arrival in a Member State's territory of a person holding a national long-stay visa issued by that Member State and the moment when the person receives a residence permit enabling him or her to move freely in the other Member States' territories. </inglise>
<eesti> 1) hetkest, mil liikmesriigi v&auml;ljastatud pikaajalise viisaga isik saabub selle liikmesriigi territooriumile, kuni hetkeni, kui ta saab elamisloa, mis v&otilde;imaldab tal vabalt liikuda teiste liikmesriikide territooriumil, v&otilde;ib kuluda aega; </eesti>
<inglise> (2) Steps should be taken to facilitate the free movement of holders of national long-stay visas pending the issue of their residence permits, by stipulating that such visas, which currently enable their holders to transit only once through the territories of the other Member States in order to reach the territory of the State which issued the visa, are concurrently valid as uniform short-stay visas, provided that the applicants fulfil the conditions of entry and residence laid down in the Convention implementing the Schengen Agreement of 14 June 1985 signed at Schengen on 19 June 1990. </inglise>
<eesti> 2) tuleks astuda samme, et h&otilde;lbustada siseriikliku pikaajalise viisaga isikute vaba liikumist, kuni neile elamisload v&auml;ljastatakse, n&auml;hes ette, et sellised viisad, mis praegu v&otilde;imaldavad nende omanikel p&auml;&auml;seda viisa v&auml;ljastanud riigi territooriumile teiste liikmesriikide territooriumi kaudu ainult &uuml;ks kord, kehtivad samaaegselt ka &uuml;htsete l&uuml;hiajaliste viisadena, tingimusel et taotlejad vastavad 19. juunil 1990 Schengenis allakirjutatud 14. juuni 1985. aasta Schengeni lepingu rakendamise konventsioonis s&auml;testatud sisses&otilde;idu- ja elamistingimustele; </eesti>
<inglise> (3) This measure is a first step in the harmonisation of the conditions for the issue of national long-stay visas. </inglise>
<eesti> 3) k&otilde;nealune meede on esimene samm siseriiklike pikaajaliste viisade v&auml;ljastamistingimuste &uuml;htlustamisel; </eesti>
<inglise> (4) The Convention implementing the Schengen Agreement and the Common Consular Instructions on Visas for the diplomatic missions and consular posts(3) should be amended accordingly. </inglise>
<eesti> 4) Schengeni lepingu rakendamise konventsiooni ning diplomaatilistele ja konsulaaresindustele etten&auml;htud viisasid k&auml;sitlevaid &uuml;hiseid konsulaarjuhiseid (3) tuleks vastavalt muuta; </eesti>
<inglise> (5) This instrument constitutes a development of the Schengen acquis, in accordance with the Protocol integrating the Schengen acquis into the framework of the European Union, as defined in Annex A to Council Decision 1999/435/EC concerning the definition of the Schengen acquis for the purpose of determining, in conformity with the relevant provisions of the Treaty establishing the European Community and the Treaty on European Union, the legal basis for each of the provisions or decisions which constitute the acquis(4). </inglise>
<eesti> 5) k&auml;esolev &otilde;igusakt on vastavalt Schengeni acquis' Euroopa Liitu integreerimist k&auml;sitlevale protokollile osa Schengeni acquis' t&auml;iendamisest, nagu see on m&auml;&auml;ratletud n&otilde;ukogu otsuse 1999/435/E&Uuml; (Schengeni acquis' m&auml;&auml;ratlemisest, et vastavalt Euroopa &Uuml;henduse asutamislepingu ja Euroopa Liidu lepingu asjakohastele s&auml;tetele kindlaks m&auml;&auml;rata k&otilde;igi acquis'd moodustavate eeskirjade ja otsuste &otilde;iguslik alus) (4) A lisas; </eesti>
<inglise> (6) As provided for in Articles 1 and 2 of the Protocol on the position of Denmark annexed to the Treaty on European Union and to the Treaty establishing the European Community, Denmark is not participating in the adoption of this instrument and, accordingly, is neither bound by it nor subject to its application. </inglise>
<eesti> 6) Taani on Euroopa Liidu lepingule ja Euroopa &Uuml;henduse asutamislepingule lisatud Taani seisukohta k&auml;sitleva protokolli artiklite 1 ja 2 kohaselt teatanud, et ei osale k&auml;esoleva &otilde;igusakti vastuv&otilde;tmises, ning seet&otilde;ttu seda tema suhtes ei kohaldata. </eesti>
<inglise> Given that the present instrument is intended to build upon the Schengen acquis under the provisions of Title IV of the Treaty establishing the European Community, Denmark, shall, in accordance with Article 5 of the Protocol, decide within a period of six months after the Council has adopted this instrument whether it will implement this decision in its national law. </inglise>
<eesti> V&otilde;ttes arvesse, et k&auml;esoleva &otilde;igusakti eesm&auml;rk on t&auml;iendada Schengeni acquis'd vastavalt Euroopa &Uuml;henduse asutamislepingu IV jaotisele, otsustab Taani vastavalt protokolli artiklile 5 kuue kuu jooksul p&auml;rast seda, kui n&otilde;ukogu on k&auml;esoleva &otilde;igusakti vastu v&otilde;tnud, kas ta rakendab seda oma siseriiklikus &otilde;iguses; </eesti>
<inglise> (7) In relation to the Republic of Iceland and the Kingdom of Norway, this instrument constitutes a development of the Schengen acquis within the meaning of the Agreement concluded on 18 May 1999 by the Council of the European Union with these two States(5). </inglise>
<eesti> 7) Islandi Vabariigi ja Norra Kuningriigi suhtes on k&auml;esolev &otilde;igusakt osa Schengeni acquis' t&auml;iendamisest vastavalt 18. mail 1999 Euroopa Liidu N&otilde;ukogu ja k&otilde;nealuse kahe riigi vahel s&otilde;lmitud lepingule; (5) </eesti>
<inglise> (8) Pursuant to Article 1 of the Protocol on the position of the United Kingdom and Ireland annexed to the Treaty on European Union and to the Treaty establishing the European Community, Ireland and the United Kingdom are not participating in the adoption of this instrument. </inglise>
<eesti> 8) Euroopa Liidu lepingule ja Euroopa &Uuml;henduse asutamislepingule lisatud &Uuml;hendkuningriigi ja Iirimaa seisukohta k&auml;sitleva protokolli artikli 1 kohaselt ei osale Iirimaa ja &Uuml;hendkuningriik k&auml;esoleva &otilde;igusakti vastuv&otilde;tmises. </eesti>
<inglise> Consequently, and without prejudice to Article 4 of the said Protocol, the provisions of this instrument apply neither to Ireland nor to the United Kingdom, </inglise>
<eesti> Sellest tulenevalt ning ilma et see piiraks eespool nimetatud protokolli artikli 4 kohaldamist, ei kohaldata k&auml;esoleva &otilde;igusakti s&auml;tteid Iirimaa ega &Uuml;hendkuningriigi suhtes, </eesti>
<inglise> HAS ADOPTED THIS REGULATION: </inglise>
<eesti> ON VASTU V&Otilde;TNUD K&Auml;ESOLEVA M&Auml;&Auml;RUSE. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 1 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 1 </eesti>
<inglise> Article 18 of the Convention implementing the Schengen Agreement shall be replaced by the following: </inglise>
<eesti> Schengeni lepingu rakendamise konventsiooni artikkel 18 asendatakse j&auml;rgmisega: </eesti>
<inglise> "Article 18 </inglise>
<eesti> "Artikkel 18 </eesti>
<inglise> Visas for stays exceeding three months shall be national visas issued by one of the Member States in accordance with its national law. </inglise>
<eesti> Viisa kauemaks kui kolmekuuliseks viibimiseks on &uuml;he liikmesriigi poolt koosk&otilde;las tema siseriiklike &otilde;igusaktidega antav siseriiklik viisa. </eesti>
<inglise> For a period of not more than three months from their initial date of validity such visas shall be valid concurrently as uniform short-stay visas, provided that they were issued in accordance with the common conditions and criteria adopted under or pursuant to the relevant provisions of Chapter 3, section 1 and their holders fulfil the entry conditions referred to in Article 5(1) (a), (c), (d) and (e). </inglise>
<eesti> Kuni kolm kuud alates nende kehtima hakkamise kuup&auml;evast kehtivad sellised viisad samaaegselt ka &uuml;htsete l&uuml;hiajaliste viisadena, tingimusel et need v&auml;ljastati koosk&otilde;las &uuml;histe tingimuste ja kriteeriumidega, mis on vastu v&otilde;etud 3. peat&uuml;ki 1. jao asjakohaste s&auml;tete alusel v&otilde;i kohaselt, ja nende omanikud vastavad artikli 5 l&otilde;ike 1 punktides a, c, d ja e s&auml;testatud sisses&otilde;idun&otilde;uetele. </eesti>
<inglise> Otherwise, such visas shall merely enable their holders to transit through the territories of the other Member States in order to reach the territory of the Member State which issued the visa, unless the holders do not fulfil the entry conditions referred to in Article 5(1) (a), (d) and (e) or are on the national list of alerts of the Member State through whose territory they seek to transit." </inglise>
<eesti> Muudel juhtudel v&otilde;imaldab selline viisa selle omanikul s&otilde;ita ainult l&auml;bi teiste liikmesriikide territooriumi, et j&otilde;uda viisa andnud liikmesriigi territooriumile, v&auml;lja arvatud juhul, kui viisa omanik ei vasta artikli 5 l&otilde;ike 1 punktides a, d ja e nimetatud sisses&otilde;idun&otilde;uetele v&otilde;i kui liikmesriik, kelle territooriumilt l&auml;bis&otilde;itu ta taotleb, on kandnud ta sisses&otilde;idukeeluregistrisse." </eesti>
<inglise> Article 2 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 2 </eesti>
<inglise> Visas for visits exceeding three months shall be national visas issued by one of the Member States in accordance with its national legislation. </inglise>
<eesti> Viisa kauemaks kui kolmekuuliseks viibimiseks on &uuml;he liikmesriigi poolt koosk&otilde;las tema siseriiklike &otilde;igusaktidega antav siseriiklik viisa. </eesti>
<inglise> However, such visas shall, for a period of not more than three months from their initial date of validity, be valid concurrently as uniform short-stay visas, provided that they were issued in accordance with the common conditions and criteria adopted under or pursuant to the relevant provisions of Chapter 3, section 1 of the Convention implementing the Schengen Agreement and their holders fulfil the entry conditions referred to in Article 5(1) (a), (c), (d) and (e) of the said Convention and reproduced in Part IV of these Instructions. </inglise>
<eesti> Kuni kolm kuud alates nende kehtima hakkamise kuup&auml;evast kehtivad sellised viisad samaaegselt ka &uuml;htsete l&uuml;hiajaliste viisadena, tingimusel et need v&auml;ljastati koosk&otilde;las &uuml;histe tingimustele ja kriteeriumidega, mis on vastu v&otilde;etud Schengeni lepingu rakendamise konventsiooni 3. peat&uuml;ki 1. jao asjakohaste s&auml;tete alusel v&otilde;i kohaselt, ja nende omanikud vastavad k&otilde;nealuse konventsiooni artikli 5 l&otilde;ike 1 punktides a, c, d ja e s&auml;testatud ja k&auml;esolevate juhiste IV osas esitatud sisses&otilde;idun&otilde;uetele. </eesti>
<inglise> Otherwise, such visas shall merely enable their holders to transit through the territories of the other Contracting Parties in order to reach the territory of the Member State which issued the visa, unless the holders do not fulfil the entry conditions referred to in Article 5(1) (a), (d) and (e) of the Convention implementing the Schengen Agreement or are on the national list of alerts of the Member State through whose territory they seek to transit." </inglise>
<eesti> Muudel juhtudel v&otilde;imaldab selline viisa selle omanikul s&otilde;ita ainult l&auml;bi teiste liikmesriikide territooriumi, et j&otilde;uda viisa andnud liikmesriigi territooriumile, v&auml;lja arvatud juhul, kui viisa omanik ei vasta Schengeni lepingu rakendamise konventsiooni artikli 5 l&otilde;ike 1 punktides a, d ja e nimetatud sisses&otilde;idun&otilde;uetele v&otilde;i kui liikmesriik, kelle territooriumilt l&auml;bis&otilde;itu ta taotleb, on kandnud ta sisses&otilde;idukeeluregistrisse." </eesti>
<inglise> Article 3 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 3 </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall enter into force on the day following that of its publication in the Official Journal of the European Communities. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus j&otilde;ustub j&auml;rgmisel p&auml;eval p&auml;rast selle avaldamist Euroopa &Uuml;henduste Teatajas. </eesti>
<inglise> This regulation shall be binding in its entirety and directly applicable in all Member States in accordance with the Treaty establishing the European Community. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus on tervikuna siduv ja vahetult kohaldatav k&otilde;ikides liikmesriikides koosk&otilde;las Euroopa &Uuml;henduse asutamislepinguga. </eesti>
